FBIS3-57931 "drweu004_p_94002" FBIS-WEU-94-004 Document Type:Daily Report 6 Jan 1994 GREECE Papandreou Views Talks; EC Visitors Depart NC0501191094 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in Greek 1800 GMT 5 Jan 94 NC0501191094 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network Language: Greek Article Type:BFN [Excerpts] Prime Minister Andreas Papandreou has described his cooperation with European Commission President Jacques Delors as productive, useful, and effective, adding that their views coincide. The members of the Greek Government and the European Commission conferred today on the goals of the Greek Presidency and coordinating efforts to integrate the European Union. Papandreou and Theodhoros Pangalos, who is presiding over the Foreign Ministers Council, referred to the priorities of the Greek Presidency, stressing that the prevailing issues are unemployment, implementing the Maastricht Treaty, expanding the European Union, and addressing the Balkan crisis. [passage omitted] The European Commission's president and members left Athens this afternoon.
